definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + NAD+ -eq- NADP+ + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-acetylneuraminate -eq- N-acetyl-D-mannosamine + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-ethylmaleimide + 2 H+ -eq- N-ethylsuccinimide.

Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + NAD+ -eq- NADP+ + NADH + H+. The reaction is A-specific (i.e. the pro-R hydrogen is transferred from the 4-position of reduced nicotinamide cofactor) with respect to NAD+ and B-specific (i.e. the pro-S hydrogen is transferred) with respect to NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  FMNH2 + NAD(P)+ -eq- FMN + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + acceptor -eq- NADP+ + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  Lipid A-core + colanic acid -eq- MLPS.
Catalysis of the polymerization of o-antigen chains. O-antigens are tetra- and pentasaccharide repeat units of the cell walls of Gram-negative bacteria and are a component of lipopolysaccharide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-succinylbenzoate + ATP + CoA -eq- 2-succinylbenzoyl-CoA + AMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group from S-adenosyl-L-methionine to a substrate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H2O + UDP-2,3-bis(3-hydroxymyristoyl)glucosamine -eq- 2,3-bis(3-hydroxymyristoyl)-beta-D-glucosaminyl 1-phosphate + UMP.
Catalysis of the removal of an acetyl group from the 2-N position of glucosamine in the lipid A precursor UDP-3-O-(R-3-hydroxymyristoyl)-N-acetylglucosamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phosphoenolpyruvate + UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine -eq- phosphate + UDP-N-acetyl-3-O-(1-carboxyvinyl)-D-glucosamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine -eq- UDP-N-acetyl-D-mannosamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetylmuramate + NADP+ -eq- UDP-N-acetyl-3-O-(1-carboxyvinyl)-D-glucosamine + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-alanine + ATP + UDP-N-acetylmuramate -eq- ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glutamate + ATP + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanine -eq- ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  meso-2,6-diaminopimelate + ATP + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamate -eq- ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminoheptanedioate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminoheptanedioate + D-alanyl-D-alanine -eq- ADP + phosphate + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-6-carboxy-L-lysyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-D-galactopyranose -eq- UDP-D-galacto-1,4-furanose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-sugar + H2O -eq- UMP + sugar 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  [acyl-carrier protein] + H2O -eq- 4'-phosphopantetheine + apoprotein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + acetate + (citrate (pro-3S)-lyase) (thiol form) -eq- AMP + diphosphate + (citrate (pro-3S)-lyase) (acetyl form).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + (isocitrate dehydrogenase (NADP)) -eq- ADP + (isocitrate dehydrogenase (NADP)) phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UTP + (protein-PII) -eq- diphosphate + uridylyl-(protein-PII).
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetaldehyde + CoA + NAD+ -eq- acetyl-CoA + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + acetate -eq- a fatty acid anion + acetyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + acetate -eq- ADP + acetyl phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N2-acetyl-L-ornithine + H2O -eq- acetate + L-ornithine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + O-(2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho)ethanolamine -eq- [acyl-carrier protein] + O-(1-beta-acyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho)ethanolamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-3-hydroxytetradecanoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + UDP-N-acetylglucosamine -eq- [acyl-carrier protein] + UDP-3-O-(3-hydroxytetradecanoyl)-N-acetylglucosamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CTP + N-acylneuraminate -eq- diphosphate + CMP-N-acylneuraminate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H2O -eq- adenine + S-D-ribosyl-L-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  agmatine + H(2)O -eq- putrescine + urea.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-alanine -eq- D-alanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  octane hydroperoxide + NADH + H+ -eq- H2O + NAD+ + 1-octanol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-allose-6-phosphate -eq- D-allulose-6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + D-allose -eq- ADP + D-allose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha,alpha-trehalose 6-phosphate + H2O -eq- D-glucose + D-glucose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-altronate -eq- 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-gluconate + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-arabinose -eq- D-ribulose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  succinyl-CoA + L-arginine -eq- CoA + N2-succinyl-L-arginine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-arginine + H(+) -eq- agmatine + CO(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  an aromatic amino acid + 2-oxoglutarate -eq- an aromatic oxo acid + L-glutamate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  arsenate + reduced glutaredoxin -eq- arsenite + oxidized glutaredoxin. Glutaredoxin functions as the electron donor for arsenate reduction. The electron flow therefore is ( NADPH --gt- glutathione reductase (EC - 1.6.4.2) --gt- ) glutathione --gt- glutaredoxin --gt- arsenate reductase, i.e. glutathione is reduced by glutathione reductase and glutaredoxin is reduced by glutathione.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + deamido-NAD+ + NH3 -eq- AMP + diphosphate + NAD+.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of P(1),P(4)-bis(5'-nucleosyl)tetraphosphate into two nucleotides.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-aspartate -eq- fumarate + NH3.
Catalysis of the cleavage of a beta-linked aspartic residue from the N-terminus of a polypeptide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a beta-lactam + H2O -eq- a substituted beta-amino acid.
